# [NMOP](../wg/nmop.html)

## Summary

The NMOP Working Group met for a one-hour session to discuss network management operations, recent network incidents, and the applicability of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) frameworks to network management. 

Key topics included:
* An operational analysis of a recent BGP routing loop incident at Swisscom and how generative AI was used to parse the telemetry data.
* A coordination status update on the upcoming AIOps side meeting and proposed Wiki guidelines for AI/ML work within the IETF.
* Several presentations on AI-assisted network management agents, northbound task interfaces, knowledge graphs, and automated protocol testing.

